tip.text: The pulled pork burger was very oily on the base. Avoid if you dislike oily food like this. The brownie was quite good.
The views of the lake were beautiful when I visited in September 2015. However the cable car broke down when I was leaving and we waited an hour for the bus to bring us down.
Western food served here was good. I liked the aglio olio and chicken chop! Service was good and they asked for feedback when we were done. Recommended!

Must try their Original Sibu Kampua Mee dry noodles. The stall name is Ah Ma's Sarawak Kampua. Chun Kee's Hakka mee at Jalan Sayur used to be my favourite but now I think this is better. Awesome pork!
RM22 for adult, worth it!! Free flow of meat, vegetables, seafood and drinks!
They have an extensive menu, price is mid range and portion is quite big. Easily one of the best Japanese restaurant around here and can beat many of those in KL.
100 mix rice dishes here for you to choose from! Food tastes quite good and price is reasonable. Variety here is wide. Go for it!

location.neighborhood: Bangsar Park, Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Pesto, pork chop, salad, spinach cream pasta all tastes awesome!! Already my second time here. =) gets very crowded and noisy during lunch hour so be early..
Great waffles, crispy on the outside and fluffy on the inside. Tried the sally salmon and Rebecca, it was tummy warming! Come early or else you'll need to wait for a table.

formattedAddress: Block 5 (Unit 12-1), Jalan Jalil Jaya 6 (Jalil Link, Jalan Jalil Jaya 6,)

tip.text: Noodles tasted a bit bland but was quite tasty and spicy after adding some of their sauce. Pork satay is a must try!
The sushi sets are delicious and value for money! Presentation is good and staff are very friendly. Will be back for more!! =D
Nice view from cable car, and after that keep climbing for more picturesque sceneries!

contact.facebookName: Mojo Restaurant & Bar, Asian Heritage Row KL

tip.text: Set lunch is only RM9.90! Come on Monday, Wednesday or Friday to taste their Nyonya Laksa.. Tuesday or Friday for Mee Siam. Peranakan ale drink is good too. :) I'll be back.
Just opened! Customised Magnum ice creams. Crazy queue.. be prepared to wait.
A lovely park for an evening or morning stroll in the middle of the city. You can see ducks, birds and squirrels inhabiting this park which is a pretty sight.

venue.name: Daan Forest Park (大安森林公園)

tip.text: One of the best pineapple cakes in Taiwan as claimed, sometimes there will be a queue outside the store to go in. Pastry is not too sweet and they have quite a good variety. Sun cakes were yummy too.
Nice place for breakfast.. cheap and yummy.

The pork chop fried rice was delicious and so was the xiao long bao. After trying the din tai fung in Taipei's original branch (Xinyi), I have to say I prefer the food in KL's outlet. Just my opinion.

venue.name: Din Tai Fung (Din Tai Fung (鼎泰豐))

tip.text: Typical shopping mall with branded shops everywhere. It's expensive to go up to the observatory tower. You can take a hike up the elephant trail and get an equally good view of the city.

tip.text: Eat all you can! Ingredients are fresh and of good quality such as their angus beef, scallops, fish, haagen dazs, movenpick etc. You have a time limit of 2 hours.

venue.name: 馬辣頂級麻辣鴛鴦火鍋

tip.text: Come before 12pm to avoid the lunch crowd. The taste is quite different from Malaysian version of beef noodle and quite pricey. Mine was 220twd a bowl.

venue.name: Yong Kang Beef Noodle (永康牛肉麵)

tip.text: Know what you want to order before approaching the staff. He will then give you a poker card as your waiting number. Soya bean sugar level can be selected. Xiao long bao and meat mantao was delicious.
Good and fresh Japanese food for a reasonable price. Will come again! The unagi rice was yummy.
